We recommended that Management:
Designate certain personnel to undergo training on how to properly conduct the inventory-taking as prescribed by the above-provided guidelines.
Subsequently thereon, create an Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of all PPEs;
Prepare and submit the approved Physical Inventory Plan to the COA Audit Team at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory-taking activities;
Ensure full implementation of "One-time cleansing of PPE accounts" as provided for in COA Circular 2020-006.

We recommended that Management:
Maximize the utilization of LDRRMF for disaster preparedness, prevention, and mitigation;
Properly plan and determine projects and activities to avoid issues and problems, hence maximizing the potential benefit that could be derived therefrom and addressing the urgent needs of the Municipality's constituents.

We recommended Management to: 

Regulate the roaming-around fish and meat vendors within the Municipality and penalize them in consonance with pertinent ordinances;

Designate specific Office or Officer to manage/ maintain the cleanliness and sanitation of the Public Market and Terminal;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to strengthen the control measures in collecting the stall rental fees by providing a contract of Lease between the LGU and the Public Market Stallholders; and

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to strictly impose the prompt collection of the balances from the delinquent stallholders in consonance with the 2013 Revised Revenue Code of Lingig.

We recommended that Management:

Require the Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly signed certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible every beginning of the year for recording purposes;

Direct, if necessary, the Municipal Treasurer to make representation with the proper authorities for the hiring of additional personnel to augment the existing manpower resources of the Municipal Treasurer’s Office;

Require the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries with regards to the affected accounts and ensure that issues concerning system errors be properly referred to the system administrator.

