We recommended that management:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare subsidiary ledger for every government projects implemented to monitor the actual cost incurred; and reconcile the cost incurred to the status of government projects implemented;

Instruct the Municipal Engineer to submit the status report of all implemented government projects, prepare the necessary documentation, and reconcile to the records of the Municipal Accountant for preparation of adjusting entry, if appropriate.

We recommended that:

Local Development Council and offices concerned to be specific in the formulation of development projects otherwise, ensure that all implemented projects described in generic terms are duly supported with SB resolution in compliance to Section 22 (c) of the Republic Act No. 7160 and COA Memorandum No. 2010-14; 

The Municipal Budget and Municipal Accountant ensure that approved SB Resolutions are submitted before processing disbursement of funds charged against the appropriations of PPAs stated in generic terms.

We recommended that:

The Municipal Treasurer to strictly monitor the collections and remittances of the revenue collectors and instruct the revenue collectors to remit their collections daily and intact;

The Municipal Treasurer ensure that collections made from the previous accountable forms are remitted and/or deposited before granting the requisition of additional accountable form to prevent accumulation of unremitted collections;

The Revenue Collectors to report and record promptly their collections and remittances on their cashbook.

We recommended that:

The Requisitioning Office to indicate the essential information on the preparation of Purchase Request;

The Municipal Treasurer ensures that Purchase Request is completely filled-up;

The Municipal Accountant ensure that all supporting documents are complete, properly filled-up all the essential data and duly acknowledged by the supplier before processing the disbursement of government funds.

